SIMPLE: intellectualize
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intellectualize
<hw>In`tel*lec"tu*al*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To treat in an intellectual manner; to discuss intellectually; to
reduce to intellectual form; to express intellectually; to
idealize.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sentiment is <qex>intellectualized</qex> emotion.</q>
<rj><qau>Lowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To endow with intellect; to bestow intellectual
qualities upon; to cause to become intellectual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intellectually</ent>⟦br⟧
